{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:psalms.55",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 55,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 55 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:1",
      "text": "Give ear to my prayer, O God; and hide not thyself from my supplication.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:2",
      "text": "Attend unto me, and hear me: I mourn in my complaint, and make a noise;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:3",
      "text": "Because of the voice of the enemy, because of the oppression of the wicked: for they cast iniquity upon me, and in wrath they hate me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:4",
      "text": "My heart is sore pained within me: and the terrors of death are fallen upon me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:5",
      "text": "Fearfulness and trembling are come upon me, and horror hath overwhelmed me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:6",
      "text": "And I said, Oh that I had wings like a dove! for then would I fly away, and be at rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:7",
      "text": "Lo, then would I wander far off, and remain in the wilderness. Selah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:8",
      "text": "I would hasten my escape from the windy storm and tempest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:9",
      "text": "Destroy, O Lord, and divide their tongues: for I have seen violence and strife in the city.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:10",
      "text": "Day and night they go about it upon the walls thereof: mischief also and sorrow are in the midst of it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:11",
      "text": "Wickedness is in the midst thereof: deceit and guile depart not from her streets.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:12",
      "text": "For it was not an enemy that reproached me; then I could have borne it: neither was it he that hated me that did magnify himself against me; then I would have hid myself from him:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:13",
      "text": "But it was thou, a man mine equal, my guide, and mine acquaintance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:14",
      "text": "We took sweet counsel together, and walked unto the house of God in company.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:15",
      "text": "Let death seize upon them, and let them go down quick into hell: for wickedness is in their dwellings, and among them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:16",
      "text": "As for me, I will call upon God; and the Lord shall save me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:17",
      "text": "Evening, and morning, and at noon, will I pray, and cry aloud: and he shall hear my voice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:18",
      "text": "He hath delivered my soul in peace from the battle that was against me: for there were many with me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:19",
      "text": "God shall hear, and afflict them, even he that abideth of old. Selah. Because they have no changes, therefore they fear not God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:20",
      "text": "He hath put forth his hands against such as be at peace with him: he hath broken his covenant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:21",
      "text": "The words of his mouth were smoother than butter, but war was in his heart: his words were softer than oil, yet were they drawn swords.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:22",
      "text": "Cast thy burden upon the Lord, and he shall sustain thee: he shall never suffer the righteous to be moved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.55.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:23",
      "text": "But thou, O God, shalt bring them down into the pit of destruction: bloody and deceitful men shall not live out half their days; but I will trust in thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
